    <p>Last time I gave a quick <a href="/blog/drupal-7-tutorial-using-entityqueue">introduction on how to create and manage queues using Entityqueue</a>. This time I'll show you how to use them with Views to display content sorted by their position in the queue.</p>
<p>First create your view like you normally would. The screenshots in this example, we are using a view of Content (aka Nodes), but this should be the same process for any entity type.<br /><img class="w550" src="//d1i58erg7nfx53.cloudfront.net/sites/default/files/entityqueue_views_01_basic_view.png" /></p>
<p>Then click add in the "Relationships" section. Select the Entityqueue relationship handler.<br /><img class="w550" src="//d1i58erg7nfx53.cloudfront.net/sites/default/files/entityqueue_views_02_add_relationship.png" /></p><ul class="links inline"><li class="0 first last"><a href="http://www.metaltoad.com/blog/drupal-7-tutorial-using-entityqueue-views" rel="tag" title="Drupal 7 Tutorial: Using Entityqueue with Views">Read more</a></li>
</ul>
